name: Lisette A. BUTLER v. Gordon J. BUTLER

parties: Lisette A. BUTLER v. Gordon J. BUTLER.

opinions.text:
ORDER
This ease is assigned to the show cause calendar.
The defendant is directed to appear on a date to be assigned and show cause why his appeal should not be dismissed since defendant’s failure to provide a transcript of the lower court proceedings renders meaningful review thereof impossible.

attorneys: Robert R. Afflick, West Warwick, for plaintiff.
Gorham & Gorham, Incorporated, Arthur M. Read II, Providence, for defendant.
casebody.head_matter:
Lisette A. BUTLER v. Gordon J. BUTLER.

Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
Nov. 19, 1981.
Robert R. Afflick, West Warwick, for plaintiff.
Gorham & Gorham, Incorporated, Arthur M. Read II, Providence, for defendant.
